{
  "stem": "20083.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so even though he had had a stroke and he was mentally [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] active again, he realized, too, that he probably would never see me again.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he said the only way I could save my life is for you to emigrate to England.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he really was very much in favor of my leaving him, too.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first of all, the packing of my personal belongings only probably took about one day because I could only take a suitcase weighing 25 pounds with me.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's all we could take with us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was very sad and yet happy at the same time because my mother knew it would save my life, since many-- especially during the Kristallnacht-- many Jewish boys, even as old as 15 and 16, were already arrested and sent to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they realized it was only a matter of time before it would be my turn.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so in that respect, of course, they were very happy that I could make it, could make it to freedom.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But losing my mother was the greatest blow of my life, and my sister, too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because I lived with them ever since my parents were divorced.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was, to me, waiting at the [GERMAN], the station in Berlin on the February the 8th, 1939, was a horrible experience.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Even though I knew it would save my life, I was equally sure probably that I would never see them alive again.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the same, of course, applies to my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But of course, I was not quite as close to him as to my mother and sister.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The, the day before I left, I said goodbye to them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I visited them on the [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
